      "text": [
        "2251 - وَ قَالَ اَلصَّادِقُ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : «وَدَّ مَنْ فِي اَلْقُبُورِ لَوْ أَنَّ لَهُ حَجَّةً بِالدُّنْيَا وَ مَا فِيهَا »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2251 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) said: \"Those in their graves wish they had a single Hajj, even at the cost of the world and all it contains.\""
        ]
      }
    }
